Advanced 
Encryption 
Standard 
(AES
)
 Not a Feistel structure, but processes the entire data
block as a single matrix during each round using
substitutions and permutation
 Thecipher begins and ends with an AddRoundKey stage
 Can view the cipher as alternating operations of XOR
encryption (AddRoundKey) of a block, followed by
scrambling of the block (the other three stages)
 The decryption algorithm makes use of the expanded
key in reverse order, however the decryption algorithm
is not identical to the encryption algorithm
 Final round of both encryption and decryption consists
of only three stages
