SubBytes
The forward substitute byte transformation, called SubBytes:
)
 It is a simple table lookup. AES defines a (16 * 16) matrix of byte values, called an S-box, that
contains a permutation of all possible 256 (8-bit) values.
 Each individual byte of State is mapped into a new byte in the following way:
 The leftmost 4 bits of the byte are used as a row value and the rightmost 4 bits are used as
a column value.
 These row and column values serve as indexes into the S-box to select a unique 8-bit
output value.
